body:
The skip function is unsupported in the node.js implementation of the json_protocol. This causes an error to be thrown when there is an unexpected input.

`
TJSONProtocol.prototype.skip = function(type) {
  throw new Error('skip not supported yet');
};
`
Interestingly, the compact_protocol implements the skip function, as does the JavaScript version.
This fix copies the compact_protocol implementation of the skip function.
